<div xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="trans-lostotherunits" xml:lang="en">
    <head>Lacunas, Other Units</head>
    <p>(e.g. column, page, cm, mm, etc.)</p>
    <p><specList>
        <specDesc key="gap"/>
    </specList>
        <!--<listRef>
            <ptr target="a"/>
            </listRef>--></p> 
 
    <p>Where text has been lost, but is to be measured in units other than 'character' or
        'line', it should be placed in a <gi>gap</gi> element and given a <att>reason</att>
        attribute with a value of "lost" and a <att>unit</att> attribute of "cm" or whatever
        unit the editor requires.</p>
    
    <cit>
        <quote>[...]</quote>
        <bibl corresp="#panciera">
            <biblScope>VIII.2</biblScope>
        </bibl>
        <bibl corresp="#ddbdp"/>
        <!-- etc. -->
    </cit>
    
    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples" corresp="#panciera">
        <gap reason="lost" extent="4.2" unit="cm" />
    </egXML>


    <div xml:id="trans-lostotherunits-responsibility">
    
        <head>Responsibility for this section</head>
        <listBibl>
            <bibl><respStmt>
                <resp>author</resp>
                <name>Scott Vanderbilt</name>
                <name/>
            </respStmt></bibl>
            <bibl><respStmt>
                <resp>author</resp>
                <name>Charlotte Tupman</name>
                <name/>
            </respStmt></bibl>
        </listBibl>
    </div>
</div>
